I'm using the sample mobile project to develop in a coordinate space of 480x320 and let Starling handle the scaling to 960x640 (iOS retina display).

Take the following code:

``` actionscript3
private function _initGraphics():void
{
    _body = new Image(Assets.getTexture('myTexture'));
    _body.width = 100; // Dimensions relative to 480x320 coordinate space
    _body.height = 100;
    addChild(_body);

    _body.pivotX = 50;
    _body.pivotY = 50;
    addEventListener(EnterFrameEvent.ENTER_FRAME, onFrame);
}

private function onFrame(e : EnterFrameEvent):void
{
    _body.rotation += 0.1;
}
```

Clearly this should rotate about the centre of the image and it works fine when run at 480x360. However, when I run it at 960x640 or on my iPhone 4 it clearly pivots around another point entirely, closer to the bottom right of the Image. I tried changing pivotX/pivotY to 100 each and it displays correctly at the high resolution but incorrectly at the low resolution. This leads me to believe that perhaps Image wasn't updated properly when contentScaleFactor came out.

I should note that if I wrap the Image in a Sprite and set pivotX/pivotY on the Sprite instead, it works fine it both resolutions.

